<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (ECSC, EEC, EURATOM) No 4063/88 of 21 December 1988 laying down provisions for applying Article 46a of the Conditions of Employment of staff of the European Centre for the Development of Vocational Training </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 4063/88, millega n&auml;hakse ette Euroopa Kutse&otilde;ppe Arenduskeskuse personali teenistustingimuste artikli 46a rakenduss&auml;tted 21. detsember 1988 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 1859/76 of 29 June 1976 laying down the Conditions of Employment of staff of the European Centre for the Development of Vocational Training (1), as last amended by Council Regulation (Euratom, ECSC, EEC) No 679/87 (2), and in particular Article 46a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1976. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 1859/76, millega kehtestatakse Euroopa Kutse&otilde;ppe Arenduskeskuse personali teenistustingimused, (1) viimati muudetud n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusega (Euratom, EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;) nr 679/87, (2) eriti selle artiklit 46a, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Committee of Experts provided for in paragraph 2 of that Article 46a, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse nimetatud artikli 46a l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud eksperdikomitee arvamust </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 46a of the Conditions of Employment of Staff of the European Centre for the Development of Vocational Training sets out the conditions for granting an unemployment allowance to former staff members who are unemployed following termination of service with the Centre; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Euroopa Kutse&otilde;ppe Arenduskeskuse personali teenistuseeskirjade artikliga 46a n&auml;hakse ette tingimused t&ouml;&ouml;tustoetuse maksmiseks endistele t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, kes p&auml;rast t&ouml;&ouml;suhte l&otilde;petamist keskuses on j&auml;&auml;nud t&ouml;&ouml;ta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is for the Commission to lay down such provisions as it deems necessary for applying paragraph 2 of that Article 46a; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjon peab kehtestama tingimused, mida ta peab vajalikuks nimetatud artikli 46a l&otilde;ike 2 kohaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 91/88 (3) lays down provisions for implementing Article 28a of the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European communities, which is identical to Article 46a of the Conditions of Employment of Staff of the European Centre for the Development of Vocational Training, </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 91/88 (3) n&auml;hakse ette Euroopa Kutse&otilde;ppe Arenduskeskuse personali teenistuseeskirjade artikliga 64a identse Euroopa &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimuste artikli 28a rakenduss&auml;tted, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 91/88 with the exception of Article 5 thereof, shall apply by analogy to staff of the European Centre for the development of Vocational Training. </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa Kutse&otilde;ppe Arenduskeskuse personali suhtes kohaldatakse analoogia p&otilde;hjal m&auml;&auml;ruse (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 91/88 s&auml;tteid, v&auml;lja arvatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikkel 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the 20th day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 20. p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. Br&uuml;ssel, 21. detsember 1988 </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 21 December 1988. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni nimel Henning CHRISTOPHERSEN </eesti>
